{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1190,"text":"I'd like to introduce you\nto an emerging area of science,"},{"time":5742,"text":"one that is still speculative\nbut hugely exciting,"},{"time":9709,"text":"and certainly one\nthat's growing very rapidly."},{"time":13448,"text":"Quantum biology\nasks a very simple question:"},{"time":17520,"text":"Does quantum mechanics --"},{"time":18894,"text":"that weird and wonderful\nand powerful theory"},{"time":22220,"text":"of the subatomic world\nof atoms and molecules"},{"time":24932,"text":"that underpins so much\nof modern physics and chemistry --"},{"time":28444,"text":"also play a role inside the living cell?"},{"time":31880,"text":"In other words: Are there processes,\nmechanisms, phenomena"},{"time":35983,"text":"in living organisms\nthat can only be explained"},{"time":39995,"text":"with a helping hand\nfrom quantum mechanics?"},{"time":43546,"text":"Now, quantum biology isn't new;"},{"time":45207,"text":"it's been around since the early 1930s."},{"time":47928,"text":"But it's only in the last decade or so\nthat careful experiments --"},{"time":51667,"text":"in biochemistry labs,\nusing spectroscopy --"},{"time":55155,"text":"have shown very clear, firm evidence\nthat there are certain specific mechanisms"},{"time":62042,"text":"that require quantum mechanics\nto explain them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65674,"text":"Quantum biology brings together\nquantum physicists, biochemists,"},{"time":69027,"text":"molecular biologists --\nit's a very interdisciplinary field."},{"time":72692,"text":"I come from quantum physics,\nso I'm a nuclear physicist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76645,"text":"I've spent more than three decades"},{"time":78934,"text":"trying to get my head\naround quantum mechanics."},{"time":81887,"text":"One of the founders\nof quantum mechanics, Niels Bohr,"},{"time":84404,"text":"said, If you're not astonished by it,\nthen you haven't understood it."},{"time":88237,"text":"So I sort of feel happy\nthat I'm still astonished by it."},{"time":91104,"text":"That's a good thing."},{"time":92873,"text":"But it means I study the very\nsmallest structures in the universe --"},{"time":99782,"text":"the building blocks of reality."},{"time":101881,"text":"If we think about the scale of size,"},{"time":105120,"text":"start with an everyday object\nlike the tennis ball,"},{"time":108096,"text":"and just go down orders\nof magnitude in size --"},{"time":111021,"text":"from the eye of a needle down to a cell,\ndown to a bacterium, down to an enzyme --"},{"time":116242,"text":"you eventually reach the nano-world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117995,"text":"Now, nanotechnology may be\na term you've heard of."},{"time":120841,"text":"A nanometer is a billionth of a meter."},{"time":124560,"text":"My area is the atomic nucleus,\nwhich is the tiny dot inside an atom."},{"time":128954,"text":"It's even smaller in scale."},{"time":130910,"text":"This is the domain of quantum mechanics,"},{"time":132852,"text":"and physicists and chemists\nhave had a long time"},{"time":135392,"text":"to try and get used to it."},{"time":137248,"text":"Biologists, on the other hand,\nhave got off lightly, in my view."},{"time":142071,"text":"They are very happy with their\nballs-and-sticks models of molecules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146426,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147532,"text":"The balls are the atoms, the sticks\nare the bonds between the atoms."},{"time":150754,"text":"And when they can't build them\nphysically in the lab,"},{"time":153272,"text":"nowadays, they have\nvery powerful computers"},{"time":155688,"text":"that will simulate a huge molecule."},{"time":157679,"text":"This is a protein made up\nof 100,000 atoms."},{"time":162003,"text":"It doesn't really require much in the way\nof quantum mechanics to explain it."},{"time":167695,"text":"Quantum mechanics\nwas developed in the 1920s."},{"time":170965,"text":"It is a set of beautiful and powerful\nmathematical rules and ideas"},{"time":177869,"text":"that explain the world of the very small."},{"time":180501,"text":"And it's a world that's very different\nfrom our everyday world,"},{"time":183897,"text":"made up of trillions of atoms."},{"time":185440,"text":"It's a world built\non probability and chance."},{"time":189818,"text":"It's a fuzzy world."},{"time":191144,"text":"It's a world of phantoms,"},{"time":192898,"text":"where particles can also behave\nlike spread-out waves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198157,"text":"If we imagine quantum mechanics\nor quantum physics, then,"},{"time":201043,"text":"as the fundamental\nfoundation of reality itself,"},{"time":206281,"text":"then it's not surprising that we say"},{"time":208035,"text":"quantum physics underpins\norganic chemistry."},{"time":210479,"text":"After all, it gives us\nthe rules that tell us"},{"time":212623,"text":"how the atoms fit together\nto make organic molecules."},{"time":215288,"text":"Organic chemistry,\nscaled up in complexity,"},{"time":218551,"text":"gives us molecular biology,\nwhich of course leads to life itself."},{"time":222174,"text":"So in a way, it's sort of not surprising."},{"time":224175,"text":"It's almost trivial."},{"time":225413,"text":"You say, \"Well, of course life ultimately\nmust depend of quantum mechanics.\""},{"time":230141,"text":"But so does everything else."},{"time":232555,"text":"So does all inanimate matter,\nmade up of trillions of atoms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236501,"text":"Ultimately, there's a quantum level"},{"time":241403,"text":"where we have to delve into\nthis weirdness."},{"time":243610,"text":"But in everyday life,\nwe can forget about it."},{"time":246404,"text":"Because once you put together\ntrillions of atoms,"},{"time":249627,"text":"that quantum weirdness\njust dissolves away."},{"time":255288,"text":"Quantum biology isn't about this."},{"time":257881,"text":"Quantum biology isn't this obvious."},{"time":260461,"text":"Of course quantum mechanics\nunderpins life at some molecular level."},{"time":265254,"text":"Quantum biology is about looking\nfor the non-trivial --"},{"time":271282,"text":"the counterintuitive ideas\nin quantum mechanics --"},{"time":275782,"text":"and to see if they do, indeed,\nplay an important role"},{"time":278821,"text":"in describing the processes of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282653,"text":"Here is my perfect example\nof the counterintuitiveness"},{"time":287897,"text":"of the quantum world."},{"time":289367,"text":"This is the quantum skier."},{"time":290642,"text":"He seems to be intact,\nhe seems to be perfectly healthy,"},{"time":293306,"text":"and yet, he seems to have gone around\nboth sides of that tree at the same time."},{"time":297457,"text":"Well, if you saw tracks like that"},{"time":299144,"text":"you'd guess it was some\nsort of stunt, of course."},{"time":301477,"text":"But in the quantum world,\nthis happens all the time."},{"time":304864,"text":"Particles can multitask,\nthey can be in two places at once."},{"time":307914,"text":"They can do more than one thing\nat the same time."},{"time":310266,"text":"Particles can behave\nlike spread-out waves."},{"time":313298,"text":"It's almost like magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315538,"text":"Physicists and chemists have had\nnearly a century"},{"time":318311,"text":"of trying to get used to this weirdness."},{"time":321445,"text":"I don't blame the biologists"},{"time":322819,"text":"for not having to or wanting\nto learn quantum mechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325478,"text":"You see, this weirdness is very delicate;"},{"time":328700,"text":"and we physicists work very hard\nto maintain it in our labs."},{"time":333174,"text":"We cool our system down\nto near absolute zero,"},{"time":337402,"text":"we carry out our experiments in vacuums,"},{"time":339371,"text":"we try and isolate it\nfrom any external disturbance."},{"time":343602,"text":"That's very different from the warm,\nmessy, noisy environment of a living cell."},{"time":349960,"text":"Biology itself, if you think of\nmolecular biology,"},{"time":352771,"text":"seems to have done very well\nin describing all the processes of life"},{"time":356252,"text":"in terms of chemistry --\nchemical reactions."},{"time":358762,"text":"And these are reductionist,\ndeterministic chemical reactions,"},{"time":363636,"text":"showing that, essentially, life is made\nof the same stuff as everything else,"},{"time":368774,"text":"and if we can forget about quantum\nmechanics in the macro world,"},{"time":371858,"text":"then we should be able to forget\nabout it in biology, as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375706,"text":"Well, one man begged\nto differ with this idea."},{"time":380062,"text":"Erwin Schrödinger,\nof Schrödinger's Cat fame,"},{"time":383555,"text":"was an Austrian physicist."},{"time":384896,"text":"He was one of the founders\nof quantum mechanics in the 1920s."},{"time":388663,"text":"In 1944, he wrote a book\ncalled \"What is Life?\""},{"time":391839,"text":"It was tremendously influential."},{"time":393594,"text":"It influenced Francis Crick\nand James Watson,"},{"time":396499,"text":"the discoverers of the double-helix\nstructure of DNA."},{"time":399343,"text":"To paraphrase a description\nin the book, he says:"},{"time":403035,"text":"At the molecular level,\nliving organisms have a certain order,"},{"time":408845,"text":"a structure to them that's very different"},{"time":412101,"text":"from the random thermodynamic jostling\nof atoms and molecules"},{"time":416861,"text":"in inanimate matter\nof the same complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421504,"text":"In fact, living matter seems to behave\nin this order, in a structure,"},{"time":426542,"text":"just like inanimate matter\ncooled down to near absolute zero,"},{"time":430400,"text":"where quantum effects\nplay a very important role."},{"time":434280,"text":"There's something special\nabout the structure -- the order --"},{"time":438464,"text":"inside a living cell."},{"time":440048,"text":"So, Schrödinger speculated that maybe\nquantum mechanics plays a role in life."},{"time":446096,"text":"It's a very speculative,\nfar-reaching idea,"},{"time":449545,"text":"and it didn't really go very far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453536,"text":"But as I mentioned at the start,"},{"time":455093,"text":"in the last 10 years, there have been\nexperiments emerging,"},{"time":457916,"text":"showing where some of these\ncertain phenomena in biology"},{"time":461995,"text":"do seem to require quantum mechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463782,"text":"I want to share with you\njust a few of the exciting ones."},{"time":468215,"text":"This is one of the best-known\nphenomena in the quantum world,"},{"time":471946,"text":"quantum tunneling."},{"time":473671,"text":"The box on the left shows\nthe wavelike, spread-out distribution"},{"time":478084,"text":"of a quantum entity --\na particle, like an electron,"},{"time":480869,"text":"which is not a little ball\nbouncing off a wall."},{"time":484530,"text":"It's a wave that has a certain probability\nof being able to permeate"},{"time":489293,"text":"through a solid wall, like a phantom\nleaping through to the other side."},{"time":492723,"text":"You can see a faint smudge of light\nin the right-hand box."},{"time":497773,"text":"Quantum tunneling suggests that a particle\ncan hit an impenetrable barrier,"},{"time":502409,"text":"and yet somehow, as though by magic,"},{"time":504893,"text":"disappear from one side\nand reappear on the other."},{"time":507658,"text":"The nicest way of explaining it is\nif you want to throw a ball over a wall,"},{"time":511933,"text":"you have to give it enough energy\nto get over the top of the wall."},{"time":515534,"text":"In the quantum world,\nyou don't have to throw it over the wall,"},{"time":518616,"text":"you can throw it at the wall,\nand there's a certain non-zero probability"},{"time":522047,"text":"that it'll disappear on your side,\nand reappear on the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525394,"text":"This isn't speculation, by the way."},{"time":527096,"text":"We're happy -- well, \"happy\"\nis not the right word --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530516,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532585,"text":"we are familiar with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534227,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":536996,"text":"Quantum tunneling\ntakes place all the time;"},{"time":539314,"text":"in fact, it's the reason our Sun shines."},{"time":542655,"text":"The particles fuse together,"},{"time":544188,"text":"and the Sun turns hydrogen\ninto helium through quantum tunneling."},{"time":549464,"text":"Back in the 70s and 80s, it was discovered\nthat quantum tunneling also takes place"},{"time":554708,"text":"inside living cells."},{"time":556290,"text":"Enzymes, those workhorses of life,\nthe catalysts of chemical reactions --"},{"time":562580,"text":"enzymes are biomolecules that speed up\nchemical reactions in living cells,"},{"time":566770,"text":"by many, many orders of magnitude."},{"time":568497,"text":"And it's always been a mystery\nhow they do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571650,"text":"Well, it was discovered"},{"time":572863,"text":"that one of the tricks that enzymes\nhave evolved to make use of,"},{"time":577739,"text":"is by transferring subatomic particles,\nlike electrons and indeed protons,"},{"time":582991,"text":"from one part of a molecule\nto another via quantum tunneling."},{"time":588333,"text":"It's efficient, it's fast,\nit can disappear --"},{"time":591208,"text":"a proton can disappear from one place,\nand reappear on the other."},{"time":594343,"text":"Enzymes help this take place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596548,"text":"This is research that's been\ncarried out back in the 80s,"},{"time":599255,"text":"particularly by a group\nin Berkeley, Judith Klinman."},{"time":603316,"text":"Other groups in the UK\nhave now also confirmed"},{"time":605545,"text":"that enzymes really do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609048,"text":"Research carried out by my group --"},{"time":611621,"text":"so as I mentioned,\nI'm a nuclear physicist,"},{"time":614079,"text":"but I've realized I've got these tools\nof using quantum mechanics"},{"time":617158,"text":"in atomic nuclei, and so can apply\nthose tools in other areas as well."},{"time":623404,"text":"One question we asked"},{"time":625238,"text":"is whether quantum tunneling\nplays a role in mutations in DNA."},{"time":629843,"text":"Again, this is not a new idea;\nit goes all the way back to the early 60s."},{"time":633527,"text":"The two strands of DNA,\nthe double-helix structure,"},{"time":636512,"text":"are held together by rungs;\nit's like a twisted ladder."},{"time":639359,"text":"And those rungs of the ladder\nare hydrogen bonds --"},{"time":642890,"text":"protons, that act as the glue\nbetween the two strands."},{"time":646704,"text":"So if you zoom in, what they're doing\nis holding these large molecules --"},{"time":651478,"text":"nucleotides -- together."},{"time":654130,"text":"Zoom in a bit more."},{"time":655304,"text":"So, this a computer simulation."},{"time":657855,"text":"The two white balls\nin the middle are protons,"},{"time":661421,"text":"and you can see that\nit's a double hydrogen bond."},{"time":663744,"text":"One prefers to sit on one side;\nthe other, on the other side"},{"time":667082,"text":"of the two strands of the vertical lines\ngoing down, which you can't see."},{"time":672410,"text":"It can happen that\nthese two protons can hop over."},{"time":675829,"text":"Watch the two white balls."},{"time":677748,"text":"They can jump over to the other side."},{"time":680239,"text":"If the two strands of DNA then separate,\nleading to the process of replication,"},{"time":685909,"text":"and the two protons\nare in the wrong positions,"},{"time":689132,"text":"this can lead to a mutation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691204,"text":"This has been known for half a century."},{"time":693100,"text":"The question is: How likely\nare they to do that,"},{"time":695467,"text":"and if they do, how do they do it?"},{"time":697869,"text":"Do they jump across,\nlike the ball going over the wall?"},{"time":700912,"text":"Or can they quantum-tunnel across,\neven if they don't have enough energy?"},{"time":705089,"text":"Early indications suggest that\nquantum tunneling can play a role here."},{"time":709365,"text":"We still don't know yet\nhow important it is;"},{"time":711513,"text":"this is still an open question."},{"time":714199,"text":"It's speculative,"},{"time":715373,"text":"but it's one of those questions\nthat is so important"},{"time":718040,"text":"that if quantum mechanics\nplays a role in mutations,"},{"time":720510,"text":"surely this must have big implications,"},{"time":722833,"text":"to understand certain types of mutations,"},{"time":725551,"text":"possibly even those that lead\nto turning a cell cancerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730803,"text":"Another example of quantum mechanics\nin biology is quantum coherence,"},{"time":736126,"text":"in one of the most\nimportant processes in biology,"},{"time":738503,"text":"photosynthesis: plants\nand bacteria taking sunlight,"},{"time":742468,"text":"and using that energy to create biomass."},{"time":746215,"text":"Quantum coherence is the idea\nof quantum entities multitasking."},{"time":750912,"text":"It's the quantum skier."},{"time":752540,"text":"It's an object that behaves like a wave,"},{"time":755516,"text":"so that it doesn't just move\nin one direction or the other,"},{"time":758442,"text":"but can follow multiple pathways\nat the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762708,"text":"Some years ago,\nthe world of science was shocked"},{"time":766648,"text":"when a paper was published\nshowing experimental evidence"},{"time":770256,"text":"that quantum coherence\ntakes place inside bacteria,"},{"time":774056,"text":"carrying out photosynthesis."},{"time":775766,"text":"The idea is that the photon,\nthe particle of light, the sunlight,"},{"time":778854,"text":"the quantum of light\ncaptured by a chlorophyll molecule,"},{"time":782222,"text":"is then delivered to what's called\nthe reaction center,"},{"time":784837,"text":"where it can be turned into\nchemical energy."},{"time":786925,"text":"And in getting there,\nit doesn't just follow one route;"},{"time":789597,"text":"it follows multiple pathways at once,"},{"time":791836,"text":"to optimize the most efficient way\nof reaching the reaction center"},{"time":796197,"text":"without dissipating as waste heat."},{"time":799228,"text":"Quantum coherence taking place\ninside a living cell."},{"time":802561,"text":"A remarkable idea,"},{"time":804705,"text":"and yet evidence is growing almost weekly,\nwith new papers coming out,"},{"time":810964,"text":"confirming that this\ndoes indeed take place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813555,"text":"My third and final example\nis the most beautiful, wonderful idea."},{"time":818318,"text":"It's also still very speculative,\nbut I have to share it with you."},{"time":822405,"text":"The European robin\nmigrates from Scandinavia"},{"time":827041,"text":"down to the Mediterranean, every autumn,"},{"time":829700,"text":"and like a lot of other\nmarine animals and even insects,"},{"time":833097,"text":"they navigate by sensing\nthe Earth's magnetic field."},{"time":838968,"text":"Now, the Earth's magnetic field\nis very, very weak;"},{"time":841419,"text":"it's 100 times weaker\nthan a fridge magnet,"},{"time":843523,"text":"and yet it affects the chemistry --\nsomehow -- within a living organism."},{"time":849932,"text":"That's not in doubt --\na German couple of ornithologists,"},{"time":853762,"text":"Wolfgang and Roswitha Wiltschko,\nin the 1970s, confirmed that indeed,"},{"time":858046,"text":"the robin does find its way by somehow\nsensing the Earth's magnetic field,"},{"time":862047,"text":"to give it directional information --\na built-in compass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865398,"text":"The puzzle, the mystery was:\nHow does it do it?"},{"time":868351,"text":"Well, the only theory in town --"},{"time":871405,"text":"we don't know if it's the correct theory,\nbut the only theory in town --"},{"time":874865,"text":"is that it does it via something\ncalled quantum entanglement."},{"time":878567,"text":"Inside the robin's retina --"},{"time":880965,"text":"I kid you not -- inside the robin's retina\nis a protein called cryptochrome,"},{"time":885221,"text":"which is light-sensitive."},{"time":886625,"text":"Within cryptochrome, a pair of electrons\nare quantum-entangled."},{"time":890588,"text":"Now, quantum entanglement\nis when two particles are far apart,"},{"time":893844,"text":"and yet somehow remain\nin contact with each other."},{"time":896991,"text":"Even Einstein hated this idea;"},{"time":898461,"text":"he called it \"spooky action\nat a distance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":900524,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":902429,"text":"So if Einstein doesn't like it,\nthen we can all be uncomfortable with it."},{"time":905896,"text":"Two quantum-entangled electrons\nwithin a single molecule"},{"time":908773,"text":"dance a delicate dance"},{"time":910268,"text":"that is very sensitive\nto the direction the bird flies"},{"time":912833,"text":"in the Earth's magnetic field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914848,"text":"We don't know if it's\nthe correct explanation,"},{"time":917482,"text":"but wow, wouldn't it be exciting\nif quantum mechanics helps birds navigate?"},{"time":923069,"text":"Quantum biology is still in it infancy."},{"time":925814,"text":"It's still speculative."},{"time":929742,"text":"But I believe it's built on solid science."},{"time":933917,"text":"I also think that\nin the coming decade or so,"},{"time":937750,"text":"we're going to start to see\nthat actually, it pervades life --"},{"time":942615,"text":"that life has evolved tricks\nthat utilize the quantum world."},{"time":948026,"text":"Watch this space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949478,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950659,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}